In [62]:

@time for i = 1:length(list)
     = list[i]
    hatSVM[:, i] = svm(ctr, Xtr, , 1)
    errSVM[i] = 1.0 - sum(cte .== sign(Xte * hatSVM[:, i])) / length(cte)
end

#
# This function fits lp regression with responses y and design matrix X
# possibly with Lasso penalty
#
function lpreg(y::Vector{Float64}, X::Matrix{Float64},
               p::Float64, ::Float64=0.0)

  # Create optimization variables
  hat = Variable(size(X, 2))
  # Set up optmization problem
  problem = minimize(norm(y - X * hat, p) +  * norm(hat[2:end], 1))
  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  hat.value

end

#
# This function fits -quantile regression with responses y and design matrix X
# possibily with Lasso penalty
#
function quantreg(y::Vector{Float64}, X::Matrix{Float64},
                  ::Float64, ::Float64=0.0)

  # Create optimization variables
  hat = Variable(size(X, 2))
  res = Variable(size(X, 1))
  # Set up optmization problem
  problem = minimize(sum( * pos(res) - (1.0 - ) * neg(res)) +
                      * sum(abs(hat[2:end])))
  problem.constraints += y - X * hat == res
  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  hat.value

end

#
# This function computes Dantzig selector solution with responses y
# and design matrix X
#
function dantzig(y::Vector{Float64}, X::Matrix{Float64}, ::Float64=0.0)

  # Create optimization variables
  hat = Variable(size(X, 2))
  # Set up optmization problem
  problem = minimize(norm(X' * (y - X * hat), Inf))
  problem.constraints += sum(abs(hat[2:end])) <= 
  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  hat.value

end

#
# This function computes SVM solution with responses y
# and design matrix X
#
function svm(y::Vector{Float64}, X::Matrix{Float64}, ::Float64, p::Int=1)

  # Create optimization variables
  hat = Variable(size(X, 2))
  # Set up optmization problem
  problem = minimize(sum(pos(1.0 - y .* (X * hat))))
  problem.constraints += norm(hat[2:end], p) <= 
  # Solve the problem by calling solve
  solve!(problem)
  # Return
  hat.value

end
